<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-2720] XmlConverter omits XML declaration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-2720</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.camel.converter.jaxp.XmlConverter is hardcoded to omit XML declaration when converting DOM document to string. Character encoding information is lost that way.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally there should be a way to override default output properties. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://fisheye6.atlassian.com/browse/camel/trunk/camel-core/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/converter/jaxp/XmlConverter.java?r=HEAD&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://fisheye6.atlassian.com/browse/camel/trunk/camel-core/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/converter/jaxp/XmlConverter.java?r=HEAD&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12487314">CAMEL-2720</key>
